int, with an introduction by renowned scholar and MacLennan biographer Elspeth Cameron, this timeless story portrays characters with a realism and fascination that is as rare as it is effective.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCanadian fiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358971140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773589711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773589711/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles